# Workflow Preferences

## Git / Commits
- NEVER create a git commit automatically.
- Before committing, propose a single one-line commit message and WAIT for explicit approval.
- Only run `git commit` after the user approves the proposed message.

## Working Style
- Work step by step. Complete one focused step, then continue.
- Keep changes small and reviewable at each step.

## Stack
- React + TypeScript + TailwindCSS (Vite).
- Use functional components and keep layout pieces (Header, Footer, Sidebar/Menu) as reusable components.
